  Locus:
    Page: 266
    Verse: 6
Tags:
  - Imagination
---
Our griefs, as well as our joys, owe their strongest colors to our
imaginations. There is nothing so grievous to be borne that pondering upon
it will not make it heavier; and there is no pleasure so vivid that the
animation of fancy cannot liven it.
